article.headline: No. 25 Wyoming tops TWU in Wyoming Shootout
article.story:
CASPER, Wyo. -- Jodi Bolerjack and Hanna Zavecz each scored
16 points to help Wyoming (No. 25 ESPN/USA Today, No. 24 AP) beat Texas Woman's University 75-60 on
Saturday in the Wyoming Shootout.

	   An 11-0 run midway through the second half gave the 
Cowgirls (9-1) their biggest lead of the game, 55-33. TWU (3-5)
never came closer than 14 points after that.

	   Wyoming outrebounded the Pioneers 49-28.

	   Aubrey Vandiver added 12 points and 10 rebounds for Wyoming, and
Rebecca Vanderjagt also had 12 points for the Cowgirls.

	   Renee Renz led TWU with 19 points. Jessica Durr added 18.
